results.name: Sum of prime power divisors of n that are <= sqrt(n).
formula: G.f.: Sum_{p prime, k>=1} p^k * x^(p^(2*k)) / (1 - x^(p^k)).
mathematica: nmax = 90; CoefficientList[Series[Sum[Boole[PrimePowerQ[k]] k x^(k^2)/(1 - x^k), {k, 1, nmax}], {x, 0, nmax}], x] // Rest
program: (PARI) a(n) = sumdiv(n, d, if ((d^2<=n) && isprimepower(d), d)); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Apr 03 2020
results.author: _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Apr 03 2020
